{
  "texts": [
    "If x ′ ̸ ∈ X, then by refinability there is a y ′ ⊑ x ′ such that (i) for all y ′′ ⊑ y ′, y ′′ ̸ ∈ X.",
    "By Definition 4.1, together x ′ ⊑ s x and y ′ ⊑ x ′ imply that there is a y ′′ ⊑ y ′ such that y ′′ ⊑ x.",
    "By (i), y ′′ ⊑ y ′ implies y ′′ ̸ ∈ X, which with y ′′ ⊑ x and persistence implies x ̸ ∈ X.Next, we observe that taking the ⊑ s -successors of a given possibility is a way of generating a set of possibilities that satisfies persistence and refinability.Fact 4.3 (⊑ s -generated Propositions).",
    "Given a poset ⟨S, ⊑⟩ and x ∈ S,{x ′ ∈ S | x ′ ⊑ s x} ∈ RO(S, ⊑).",
    "Since x ′ ⊑ x implies x ′ ⊑ s x, the set {x ′ ∈ S | x ′ ⊑ s x} satisfies persistence.For refinability, suppose y ̸ ∈ {x ′ ∈ S | x ′ ⊑ s x}, so y ̸ ⊑ s x, so there is a y ′ ⊑ y such that for all y ′′ ⊑ y ′, y ′′ ̸ ⊑ x."
  ]
}